('a632da78-0bff-45cc-a877-4dc9499e60c9', 'CON-CRET: The No-Bloat Alternative', 'Creatine HCl for those who cannot tolerate monohydrate. Micro-dosing at 750mg eliminates the loading phase and water retention issues.', 'Creatine Hydrochloride 750mg per serving. 59x more soluble than monohydrate. Patented formula designed for maximum absorption per milligram.', ARRAY['Micro-dose (no 5g scoops)', 'No loading phase needed', 'No bloating or water retention', 'Easy on the stomach'], 'Take 1 capsule per 100 lbs body weight. No loading phase required.', ARRAY['Less research than monohydrate', 'More expensive per gram', 'May be less effective overall', 'Lower total creatine per serving'], 'Those who experience bloating, water retention, or stomach issues from creatine monohydrate.', 'ON Micronized for proven monohydrate. Thorne for premium monohydrate.', 'Q: Is HCl really better than monohydrate? A: For those with GI issues from monohydrate, yes. But monohydrate has vastly more research. Q: Why such a small dose? A: Higher solubility theoretically means better absorption per milligram.', 7.8, '[{"name": "Steve G.", "rating": 5, "text": "Monohydrate gave me terrible bloating. CON-CRET solved that completely. No bloating at all.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-04"}, {"name": "Amy H.", "rating": 4, "text": "Great for sensitive stomachs. I notice the same strength gains without the water weight.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-16"}]'::jsonb),

